captions.text: - But here's what's good about 30
is that you drink through your mouth

instead of pouring alcohol
into a funnel into your butt.
(laughter)
That's the new craze.
(upbeat music)
- I don't consider 30 old, per say,
I consider it on the way up.

- 30 is midlife crisis and
then you find yourself.

- When I hear the age
30 I think of better,
you know, more wisdom.
- I don't, I don't want to be 30.

- It seems old, it does.
- 30 seems old.
- It does.

- I know.
(cries)
- It's okay.

That's the scary part,
is that you go to bed 29,
you wake up 30 and it's the same life.

- Everyone said midlife
crises, that's not...
- Yeah, that's the weird ones.
- It's funny, what they don't realize is
that the quarter-life crisis I feel like
is actually pretty true.

You get out of college
and then you're like. . .
- [Man] What am I doing with my life.
- [Woman] "oh shit."
- I think the quarter-life crisis is just
you have to pay rent.

- Parties will be irrelevant
because I'll be too old.
- The parties will be ending early.
- Parties will be boring.
30-year-olds just drink wine
and let's have a night watching SVU.
- Parties at 30 actually get a lot better.
- Yeah

- Because the parties
that you're going to now
are just loud music and skunk beer.
- Oh, and sweat

- And sweat.
- And shame.

- Maybe this is good
or bad but I still host
a lot of parties that go 'till 4 am.

- Where did you get that we
all drink wine all the time?
- I've had wine before.

- Wine will become your
best friend in your thirties
if maybe ditched the boxed wine.
- When you leave the party's over.

So it doesn't really
matter what time it is.
- When I leave.

- Hopefully boys will be
men by the time they're 30.
(laughter)
That's gonna be the best, or not.

I mean, maybe they need to
be, like, 35, I don't know.

- I feel like by the time I
turn 30 I really wouldn't care
what people think, at all.
- Depending on how cool my twenties are,
maybe I'll be married.

- But nobody will know
that I am 30, when I'm 30.
Everyone's gonna think I'm still 29.

- Like right now I'm still
kind of in that teenage mindset

where I feel that
everyone's criticizing me
- But when I'm 30, I just wanna live.

- We'll be the wine-night
30-year-olds who are like,

"Ugh, those 20-year-olds don't
know what they're doing."
- Uh-huh, but they sure are hot.
(laughter)

- The only thing that
I've learned from 20 to 30
is that I don't know anything.
Once you realize that you don't know shit,

- Then you know shit.
- Then you know shit.
- Yeah, you definitely come into your own

and you feel so much more
comfortable just being yourself.

- If you think that women are
gonna get better by the time

they're 30, just wait 'till
you have a 40-year-old.

- The answer is you're not gonna
be where you think you are.

- Yeah. Totes.
- Deep.
(laughter)

- [voiceover] There's one
last thing I'd like to say:

fireball is--
- [ Man in hat] Delicious.

- [Man with beard] Awful.
- [Man in hat] Oh.
- None of these fools know what the f***
they're talking about.

When I was 25 I was really depressed that in a mere 5 years I'd be 30. I

known how much better I'd feel inside my head once I hit my 30's, and how 
much more fun I'd actually have because I no longer care as much about what 
other people think of me and I'm able to really just let loose and be 
myself, I would have done it sooner.. Well, I mean..  metaphorically..  I 
also feel wayyyy cooler now than I ever did as a teenager/young adult. Your 
30's are when you really become yourself and I seriously mean that. Having 
said all of this, I'm not looking forward to 40..  lol..﻿

comments.text:
Im turning 25 yrs old this year, so i appreciate videos like this. Im half 
way there to 30 already and although i am young, I'm not THAT young 
considering what i think is expected of me by the time i reach 30 yrs old.

 My understanding is that by the time people reach 30 yrs old, they are 
expected to be more mature and be more settled in life. This means being 
done with education for the most part, have reasonable career established 
already...etc. To some, this could involve marriage and having children, 
while some never date anyone in life or some chose not to get married. For 
some, It may unfortunately mean a divorce, so they can move on and settle 
with their own life. whatever it is that is on your plate, i think by the 
time you are 30 yrs old, maturity and certain level of settlement is 
required. 

This is not to say that everyone must have x,y and z accomplished by the 
time they turn 30 yrs old... everyone's life is different and you can't 
judge anyone based on career, marital status or educational status. After 
all, life isn't a checklist right?﻿
